In the Matter of John ANTOINE, Debtor. John ANTOINE v. HEITMAN TRUST COMPANY. No. 5850. Circuit Court of Appeals, Seventh Circuit. May 7, 1936. Walter E. Wiles, of Chicago, Ill., for appellant. Hcrshenson & Hershenson, of Chicago, 111., for appellee.

Before SPARKS and ALSCHULER, Circuit Judges.

PER CURIAM.

On consideration whereof, it is now here ordered, adjudged, and decreed by this court that this appeal be, and the same is hereby, dismissed1 with costs. It is further ordered that the mandate of this court issue forthwith.
